    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1335.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 4, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 16th ultimo, No. 894,
                            together with its accompanying copy of a note of the 11th ultimo,
                            addressed to you by Earl Russell, upon the subject of the existence in
                            the provinces of Nova Scotia of an organization for the purpose of
                            destroying the ships of the United States upon the lakes and elsewhere,
                            has been received, and is approved.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
